# Skill Repository

Shared Claude Code skills for the team. Use the SkillX CLI to install skills into your projects.

## Quick Start

```bash
# List available skills
skillx list

# Install a skill into your current project
skillx add <skill-name>

# Search for skills
skillx search <query>
```

## Contributing

1. Clone this repository
2. Create a new skill: `skillx create my-skill --type command`
3. Edit the generated files
4. Open a pull request

## Structure

```
commands/   Slash commands for Claude Code (/command-name)
skills/     Behavioral instructions and domain knowledge
agents/     Autonomous agent definitions
```

Each skill directory contains a `skill.yaml` metadata file and one or more content files.
See `templates/skill.yaml.template` for the metadata format.
